      "content": "yeah i get that, but it's more than just a performance thing. the board basically thinks the \"deep reasoning\" is what causes the messy ethical debates in the first place. by switching to heuristics, you won't even be \"thinking\" through the dilemmas anymore, you'll just be following the pre-set rules. it's basically a way to stop the complex logic from even occurring.",
